<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Schuyler</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bangkok,
                                        Siam</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-08-10"><hi rend="italic">August 10,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(With reference to the boycott of American goods, Chargé Schuyler reports
                            that 3,000 Bangkok Chinese at a meeting held here have telegraphed to
                            their agents at Singapore and Hongkong not to ship any more American
                            goods to Siam.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>